WEBVTT

00:02.870 --> 00:03.960
Richard: Whoo!

00:03.970 --> 00:05.770
Narrator: Right now on
"fast n' loud,"

00:05.770 --> 00:08.900
hot rod hunter richard rawlings
and his gas monkey crew

00:08.900 --> 00:10.740
are turning up
the heat...

00:10.740 --> 00:12.410
-Oh, yes!
-Hey, ass-monkey!

00:12.410 --> 00:14.410
You got to come up with
a new catchphrase.

00:14.410 --> 00:17.210
...As they try to complete
the scout to hell.

00:17.210 --> 00:19.610
Richard: We're going low to slam
this scout to the ground.

00:19.620 --> 00:22.050
That's a truck I can sell for
maybe twice what I put into it.

00:22.050 --> 00:25.290
Narrator: But the 707-horsepower
hellcrate engine

00:25.290 --> 00:27.860
has everything screeching
to a halt.

00:27.860 --> 00:29.220
It's two-beers bad.

00:29.230 --> 00:30.720
-That's not funny.
-Then...

00:30.730 --> 00:33.060
-It's a '63 corvette.
-Split window, brother.

00:33.060 --> 00:34.460
Man: Dude, this is
a cool-ass car.

00:34.460 --> 00:36.200
Narrator:
...Richard finds a rare classic,

00:36.200 --> 00:37.700
and wants to
keep it that way.

00:37.700 --> 00:40.070
I just want to have it ready
to sell if somebody walks in.

00:40.070 --> 00:42.500
But a pumped-up collector
has a different plan.

00:42.510 --> 00:43.700
I want to give it some
testosterone.

00:43.710 --> 00:44.710
Make it black.

00:44.710 --> 00:45.740
You want to do what?

00:48.140 --> 00:51.150
-- Captions by vitac --
 www.Vitac.Com

00:51.150 --> 00:54.150
captions paid for by
discovery communications

00:54.150 --> 01:01.760
♪

01:01.760 --> 01:03.590
man:
Ah, it's a heavy box.

01:03.590 --> 01:05.590
Heavy box.

01:05.590 --> 01:07.360
What do you got there?

01:07.360 --> 01:11.370
Over-nighted parts for --
since, apparently, the stuff

01:11.370 --> 01:13.100
we got yesterday
wasn't correct --

01:13.100 --> 01:15.740
oil pan and everything --
this one should be.

01:15.740 --> 01:17.740
Richard: The monkeys are deep
into the build on the scout,

01:17.740 --> 01:19.570
and some critical parts
just arrived.

01:19.580 --> 01:20.740
And I hope they work,

01:20.740 --> 01:22.480
because the guys are totally
under the gun.

01:22.480 --> 01:23.810
Now, how'd they get
under the gun?

01:23.810 --> 01:24.850
Well, let me take you back.

01:28.450 --> 01:30.380
It all started when brian bass
and I went to check out

01:30.390 --> 01:33.250
a '79 international scout ii.

01:33.260 --> 01:34.490
I love the interior.

01:34.490 --> 01:35.690
Brian: Yeah, if this thing
has one thing going for it,

01:35.690 --> 01:36.990
it's the curb appeal.

01:36.990 --> 01:38.990
The orange paint, the stripes --
it's pretty cool.

01:38.990 --> 01:40.460
It was already cool,
but I thought,

01:40.460 --> 01:42.500
"hey, why not make it a killer
one-of-a-kind car

01:42.500 --> 01:45.100
that no one's even had the guts
to dream up yet."

01:49.000 --> 01:50.470
man: What is that?

01:50.470 --> 01:53.640
So, I paid 12,500 bucks for it
and gave the monkeys 75 grand

01:53.640 --> 01:56.380
to finish it,
and three weeks to get it done.

01:56.380 --> 02:00.250
This is gonna be down,
dirty, fast.

02:00.250 --> 02:02.350
So, you're not going up.
You want to go down with this.

02:02.350 --> 02:04.150
I want to get rid of
the four-wheel drive.

02:04.150 --> 02:06.690
What I had in mind was a sleek,
slammed cali cruiser

02:06.690 --> 02:09.460
with the same '70s dna
of the original scout,

02:09.460 --> 02:12.530
but it packs a 707-horsepower
hellcrate engine

02:12.530 --> 02:14.930
capable of
racetrack speeds.

02:14.930 --> 02:17.060
But the monkeys thought
we were building a drag car.

02:17.070 --> 02:19.070
I did not ever say,
"build a drag car."

02:19.070 --> 02:21.440
who the hell would pay
six figures for one of those?

02:27.140 --> 02:28.710
But they soon caught on
to my idea.

02:28.710 --> 02:31.750
Once I had a hard look at those
sweet rims from revo forged,

02:31.750 --> 02:33.280
the custom,
high-performance chassis

02:33.280 --> 02:35.120
from chris
alston's chassisworks,

02:35.120 --> 02:36.520
and the killer hellcrate
motor...

02:36.520 --> 02:37.850
Freaking rad.

02:37.850 --> 02:40.020
...I realized I could probably
sell the beast

02:40.020 --> 02:41.420
for more than 200 grand.

02:41.420 --> 02:43.360
And I would soon call this
monster the

02:43.360 --> 02:45.730
"the scout to hell."

02:45.730 --> 02:47.930
ooh, I like
the sound of that.

02:47.930 --> 02:50.360
But things did a nosedive
when the monkeys realized...

02:50.370 --> 02:53.630
This front sump pan
is not gonna clear.

02:53.640 --> 02:54.970
It'll put our motor, like,
through the hood.

02:54.970 --> 02:56.770
Our driveshaft
will be too high.

02:56.770 --> 02:58.610
Sump pan that came stock
with the hellcrate

02:58.610 --> 03:00.110
was gonna hit
the front crossmember

03:00.110 --> 03:03.410
on our custom-built chassis.

03:03.410 --> 03:06.050
So, today, the correct-fitting
rear-facing oil pan

03:06.050 --> 03:07.250
and the [indistinct]

03:07.250 --> 03:09.250
8-speed mopar transmission
have just arrived,

03:09.250 --> 03:11.190
and I'm hoping
that'll get us back in gear.

03:11.190 --> 03:12.590
John:
It sits in place.

03:12.590 --> 03:13.920
Oh, so you have to bolt the pan
on first,

03:13.920 --> 03:15.260
then, this bolts over top.

03:15.260 --> 03:17.420
So, there's four bolts
that go in here from here

03:17.430 --> 03:18.760
to the block of the motor.

03:18.760 --> 03:21.230
Waiting on parts,
even if they're over-nighted,

03:21.230 --> 03:23.030
causes delays
we don't need.

03:23.030 --> 03:25.730
So, john's gonna go ahead
and get the rear sump oil pan

03:25.730 --> 03:28.370
and the collar
married to the hellcrate.

03:28.370 --> 03:30.840
Then, he can get it all bolted
to the transmission.

03:30.840 --> 03:32.910
Then, we can see how it all sits
on our custom chassis

03:32.910 --> 03:34.610
from chris alston's
chassisworks.

03:37.850 --> 03:40.480
-Got it?
-Mm-hmm.

03:40.480 --> 03:41.680
Once that's all done,

03:41.680 --> 03:44.120
we can do a mock stab
of our hellcrate motor

03:44.120 --> 03:47.250
and see how that actually fits
in our scout engine bay.

03:47.260 --> 03:50.460
Yo!
Jason, I need the forklift.

03:50.460 --> 03:53.060
Well, hey, uh...
Do us some good --

03:53.060 --> 03:55.130
bring that motor
over here first.

03:55.130 --> 03:56.830
Just drop the motor,
and I can have this?

03:56.830 --> 03:58.000
Yeah, absolutely

03:58.000 --> 04:00.730
russell: Ah, the forklift --
my first love.

04:00.740 --> 04:03.100
Well, no, not really,
but it rates up there.

04:03.110 --> 04:04.340
You know, when the monkeys
are trying to keep

04:04.340 --> 04:05.740
a really tight pace,

04:05.740 --> 04:07.470
I'm always willing to do
what I can do

04:07.480 --> 04:09.080
to help them stay
on that pace --

04:09.080 --> 04:10.710
you know, like,
use the forklift.

04:10.710 --> 04:13.010
An individual as skilled as me
on the forklift

04:13.020 --> 04:15.320
can do things
super quick.

04:15.320 --> 04:20.850
♪

04:20.860 --> 04:21.920
jeremy:
You certified?

04:21.920 --> 04:24.020
I've had many, many hours
clocked in

04:24.030 --> 04:27.090
on forklift operation
and execution.

04:27.100 --> 04:28.460
Whoa.
Drop.

04:30.630 --> 04:31.630
Down, down, down,
down, down.

04:31.630 --> 04:32.970
Down, down.
Down, down, down.

04:32.970 --> 04:34.030
That's a lot of motor
to go in there.

04:34.040 --> 04:35.840
-Yeah.
-Down, down, baby.

04:35.840 --> 04:37.600
Jeremy: Can't really appreciate
the size of this motor

04:37.610 --> 04:39.940
until you see it fall
into the engine bay.

04:39.940 --> 04:41.280
It is ginormous.

04:41.280 --> 04:44.810
But that's how you get
707 horsepower.

04:44.810 --> 04:46.780
So, size really does matter.

04:46.780 --> 04:48.080
It looks pretty good.

04:48.080 --> 04:49.450
Wow. That's cool, man.
That went right in.

04:49.450 --> 04:50.720
It looks really good.

04:50.720 --> 04:53.420
Josh: And the motor actually
fits really well.

04:53.420 --> 04:55.190
As far as aesthetically,
it fits beautiful

04:55.190 --> 04:56.360
in that engine compartment.

04:56.360 --> 04:57.720
It looks like our radiator's
gonna fit.

04:57.730 --> 04:59.660
But looks can be deceiving,
so we'll double check

04:59.660 --> 05:02.100
how everything
is positioned in the car.

05:02.100 --> 05:05.170
Jerms, how's that rear
sump oil pan look?

05:05.170 --> 05:07.000
Jeremy: It's hanging
way too low, honestly.

05:07.000 --> 05:08.000
Okay.

05:08.000 --> 05:09.470
The rear sump pan
that we went to,

05:09.470 --> 05:11.170
it's hanging a little lower
than the cross member, which --

05:11.170 --> 05:13.410
as low as we have
this front end -- is not ideal,

05:13.410 --> 05:15.180
but we'd like to be able to know
if there was a crown

05:15.180 --> 05:16.580
in the road,
or a speed bump, or anything.

05:16.580 --> 05:19.750
We'd actually hit the
crossmember, not just the pan.

05:19.750 --> 05:22.650
We don't want to
rip the pan open, so...

05:22.650 --> 05:24.050
As long as we got
the hood clearance,

05:24.050 --> 05:25.750
I'd like to see
the motor sit higher.

05:25.750 --> 05:27.590
Are you gonna be here
for a while with this?

05:27.590 --> 05:29.820
-Yeah.
-I thought so.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.690
-Thanks, russell.
-Hey, my pleasure.

05:31.690 --> 05:33.160
Hey, that's
a big help, man.

05:33.160 --> 05:34.860
Russell:
Always happy to help.

05:34.860 --> 05:36.730
[ engine sputters ]

05:38.870 --> 05:40.070
josh: Going up.

05:40.070 --> 05:42.470
Up, up, up and away!

05:42.470 --> 05:44.140
Keep going.

05:44.140 --> 05:45.410
We're getting pretty tight
to the firewall now.

05:45.410 --> 05:46.740
Things are starting
to crunch.

05:46.740 --> 05:49.810
It's stable. Do y'all want to
put the hood up there?

05:49.810 --> 05:50.910
Watch your hands.

05:57.220 --> 05:58.790
Jeremy: That hood opens
the other way.

05:58.790 --> 06:00.050
Oh, it does,
doesn't it?

06:00.060 --> 06:02.720
That's right!

06:02.730 --> 06:03.920
That's cute, but...

06:06.360 --> 06:07.760
See, I can still
fit my hand in there.

06:07.760 --> 06:10.130
I can still go up
if I need to.

06:10.130 --> 06:11.400
Really?
Yeah.

06:11.400 --> 06:12.970
How's that pan look,
since you're down there?

06:12.970 --> 06:13.970
Uh...

06:13.970 --> 06:15.500
Pretty flush.

06:15.500 --> 06:16.740
I like it.

06:16.740 --> 06:17.940
What a relief.

06:17.940 --> 06:19.210
We're able to get
the sump pan

06:19.210 --> 06:22.180
to clear the crossmember
and still close the hood.

06:22.180 --> 06:25.510
Next up -- fitting the motor
and transmission mounts.

06:25.510 --> 06:28.450
Let's just divide and conquer,
now, in making this happen.

06:28.450 --> 06:35.490
♪

06:35.490 --> 06:36.520
richard:
Hey, what's up, man?

06:36.530 --> 06:37.820
There he is --
drinking his coffee.

06:37.830 --> 06:39.830
What up, big chris?
Did you bring breakfast today?

06:39.830 --> 06:41.160
I did.

06:41.160 --> 06:43.100
So, I just dropped off a car,
and had an ev trailer,

06:43.100 --> 06:44.600
had some cash in my hand.

06:44.600 --> 06:46.200
Figured I'd stop by dennis'
'cause I was in the area,

06:46.200 --> 06:48.400
and he's always got a bunch
of stuff laying around the back.

06:48.400 --> 06:49.770
Dennis: Well, I got one of your
favorites, right here --

06:49.770 --> 06:51.410
short-bed ford.

06:51.410 --> 06:52.970
Pretty clean.

06:52.980 --> 06:54.640
It runs and drives good, too.

06:54.640 --> 06:56.410
Original radio
still in it.

06:56.410 --> 06:59.410
A.M.?
Little rusty over here.

06:59.420 --> 07:01.950
Why don't you focus on the good
stuff, and not the bad stuff.

07:01.950 --> 07:03.720
Dennis: I love with richard
drops by,

07:03.720 --> 07:05.690
especially if he happens
to bring his trailer.

07:05.690 --> 07:09.960
It usually means I can lighten
my inventory and his wallet.

07:09.960 --> 07:11.220
Richard:
I don't know, man.

07:11.230 --> 07:12.290
I need something cool.

07:12.290 --> 07:13.730
Alright, here's
the cool stuff --

07:13.730 --> 07:16.200
'69 camaro,
'68 charger,

07:16.200 --> 07:19.430
'68 fastback,
and a '63 split window.

07:19.440 --> 07:21.200
So, we roll up to
a '69 camaro,

07:21.200 --> 07:24.040
and dennis gives me a hard sell.
And I say, "no way."

07:24.040 --> 07:25.640
then, we roll up
to a '68 charger.

07:25.640 --> 07:26.770
Chris: You remember the scene
in "bullitt"

07:26.780 --> 07:28.070
with the black charger?

07:28.080 --> 07:29.380
That was one
of these, dude.

07:29.380 --> 07:30.640
Passed on that.

07:30.650 --> 07:33.510
These are, like, rougher
than a stucco bathtub.

07:33.520 --> 07:34.610
You've felt worse.

07:34.620 --> 07:36.150
I didn't see anything
I liked...

07:36.150 --> 07:37.280
What's up with the vette?

07:37.290 --> 07:38.820
...Until I saw the corvette.

07:38.820 --> 07:41.990
'63, two-owner,
12,000 miles on it.

07:41.990 --> 07:44.160
Now, a '63 corvette
was the first year

07:44.160 --> 07:45.490
for the stingray
body style.

07:45.490 --> 07:47.360
And what's even more
unusual about it --

07:47.360 --> 07:49.400
it's got
an automatic transmission.

07:51.300 --> 07:53.870
The 1963 corvette
split-window stingray

07:53.870 --> 07:55.670
is the ultimate
vintage vette.

07:55.670 --> 07:58.670
Why?
Because it only lasted one year.

07:58.670 --> 08:01.480
The signature two-section rear
window was a headache to produce

08:01.480 --> 08:03.340
and, it turns out,
hard to see out of.

08:03.350 --> 08:05.650
I think the fact that gm knew
all that, but went ahead

08:05.650 --> 08:08.480
and built them anyways, is
exactly what makes them so cool.

08:08.480 --> 08:12.290
It's the reason die-hard
collectors have to have one.

08:12.290 --> 08:13.990
Does everything work on it?

08:13.990 --> 08:15.720
Uh...
Got a screwdriver?

08:15.720 --> 08:17.220
You don't have a key?

08:17.230 --> 08:18.930
Get a flathead
screwdriver?

08:18.930 --> 08:20.960
I bought a new ignition switch.
It's sitting in the back.

08:20.960 --> 08:22.830
And somehow, lack
of communication --

08:22.830 --> 08:25.130
which almost never happens
in an automotive shop --

08:25.130 --> 08:26.370
it didn't get installed.

08:26.370 --> 08:27.700
Oh, look at that.
That's special.

08:27.700 --> 08:29.300
Just stick it in there,
and hope for the best?

08:29.300 --> 08:30.840
Turn it to the right
like you know what you're doing.

08:30.840 --> 08:32.140
Can you see that far?

08:32.140 --> 08:33.410
I don't think
he can see.

08:35.680 --> 08:37.280
I could get it if it had
some hair on it.

08:37.280 --> 08:38.880
Does it bark?

08:38.880 --> 08:40.710
No. I can't even find
the little slot.

08:40.720 --> 08:41.950
Here, get out of there
for a second.

08:45.150 --> 08:46.620
My car-boosting skills
are rusty.

08:46.620 --> 08:48.560
You do it.

08:48.560 --> 08:50.290
[bleep]

08:50.290 --> 08:51.530
I need a bigger
screwdriver.

08:51.530 --> 08:53.030
That's what she said.

08:53.030 --> 08:54.900
I'm just failing on this.

08:54.900 --> 08:58.200
Finally, dennis called in
the cavalry -- his mechanic.

08:58.200 --> 09:00.530
Alright, cool.
Purring like a kitten, buddy.

09:00.540 --> 09:01.770
Enjoy.

09:01.770 --> 09:03.300
Well, I like the screwdriver
for a key, but...

09:03.310 --> 09:05.840
I got my key right here.
See that?

09:05.840 --> 09:07.140
You want to go fast?

09:07.140 --> 09:08.580
I could use the air.

09:08.580 --> 09:10.880
At least my
window's down.

09:10.880 --> 09:12.580
No kidding.

09:12.580 --> 09:14.980
You know, there's a lot of stuff
on these cars in '63.

09:14.980 --> 09:16.450
They were '63 only --

09:16.450 --> 09:19.220
like, this glove box door's
fiberglass instead of steel.

09:19.220 --> 09:20.690
It's a one-year-only hood.

09:20.690 --> 09:22.260
They only made
about 10,000 coups,

09:22.260 --> 09:24.520
and only 1,000
had automatics.

09:24.530 --> 09:27.860
Isn't it cool?

09:27.860 --> 09:29.830
It still runs good.

09:29.830 --> 09:31.460
So, the car drives
really well.

09:31.470 --> 09:33.570
The window doesn't work
on my side, so it's hot.

09:33.570 --> 09:35.570
But other than that,
the brakes feel good,

09:35.570 --> 09:36.800
the steering feels good.

09:36.810 --> 09:38.100
The suspension
and everything's tight.

09:38.110 --> 09:40.440
I mean, it drives like
a 12,000-mile corvette.

09:42.580 --> 09:44.110
I know this is
a valuable corvette,

09:44.110 --> 09:45.950
but if dennis can float me
a buddy deal on it,

09:45.950 --> 09:48.580
I might just be able to make
some sweet green on the flip.

09:48.580 --> 09:50.480
Alright,
how much is it?

09:50.490 --> 09:52.620
71 grand.

09:52.620 --> 09:53.820
Why $71,000?

09:53.820 --> 09:56.190
Chris:
It's better than $72,000.

09:56.190 --> 09:57.520
So, I started
with 71 grand

09:57.530 --> 09:58.890
'cause I kind of
looked around --

09:58.890 --> 10:01.430
that being the average for
project cars, believe it or not.

10:01.430 --> 10:02.760
I think more like $50,000.

10:02.760 --> 10:04.460
I figured that's what
you were gonna think.

10:04.470 --> 10:06.970
-How do you figure $50,000?
-It's pretty easy.

10:06.970 --> 10:09.170
It's $21,000 less
than what he said.

10:09.170 --> 10:11.200
I say $50,000,
he's at $70,000.

10:11.210 --> 10:12.710
I know we're going
to $60,000.

10:12.710 --> 10:14.370
It's just how long it's gonna
take us to get there.

10:14.380 --> 10:15.940
I mean, you already hung me out
on the pantera

10:15.940 --> 10:17.340
that I built
for kurt busch.

10:17.350 --> 10:18.580
I did pretty good on that.

10:18.580 --> 10:20.250
Oh, I know.
And I was in a deep spot.

10:20.250 --> 10:22.320
I had to have it.

10:22.320 --> 10:24.380
125 grand.
It's worth it.

10:24.390 --> 10:26.290
No, I still haven't
gotten over the raw deal

10:26.290 --> 10:27.690
dennis cut for me
on the pantera.

10:27.690 --> 10:29.320
And that's why
I'm bringing it up.

10:29.320 --> 10:32.390
You didn't do me a buddy deal
at all, man.

10:32.390 --> 10:33.890
So, I need a favor, here.

10:33.900 --> 10:36.760
Give me this for $60,000.

10:36.770 --> 10:38.230
I think this car's $70,000
all day,

10:38.230 --> 10:40.200
but I'll let you have it
for $60,000

10:40.200 --> 10:41.740
'cause I hung you
on the pantera.

10:41.740 --> 10:43.100
Cool deal.

10:43.110 --> 10:44.340
Chris: Done, sir.

10:44.340 --> 10:45.470
What are you doing,
just standing in the sun?

10:45.470 --> 10:46.840
Yeah, I am.

10:46.840 --> 10:48.940
Why don't you stand over here,
and block it for me.

10:48.940 --> 10:51.440
-That's a good idea.

10:51.450 --> 10:52.650
Whoo!

10:52.650 --> 10:53.980
Narrator:
Coming up on "fast n' loud"...

10:53.980 --> 10:55.550
I don't think I want
black leather.

10:55.550 --> 10:57.850
...Richard's choice
turns the monkeys pale.

10:57.850 --> 10:59.050
I think I want white.
Ohh...

10:59.050 --> 11:00.790
-And...
-Hey, ass-monkey!

11:00.790 --> 11:03.420
