like butt cheeks.

35:47.240 --> 35:49.040
-What?
-Most people's butt cheeks.

35:49.040 --> 35:50.440
Sorry, jeremy.

35:50.440 --> 35:52.180
At my age, my butt cheeks
ain't that tight.

35:52.180 --> 35:54.980
-I disagree.
-Oh!

35:54.980 --> 35:56.520
[ laughter ]

36:03.290 --> 36:06.860
♪

36:06.860 --> 36:09.060
[ engine revs ]

36:09.060 --> 36:11.300
♪

36:11.300 --> 36:14.100
richard: Whoo!

36:14.100 --> 36:16.100
When I first had
the big idea to turn

36:16.100 --> 36:18.740
a 1979 international
harvester scout

36:18.740 --> 36:20.440
into a one-of-a-kind scout
to hell,

36:20.440 --> 36:22.570
it was ambitious,
to say the least.

36:22.580 --> 36:26.140
♪

36:26.150 --> 36:27.450
I love the interior.

36:27.450 --> 36:28.780
Yeah, if this thing has
one thing going for it,

36:28.780 --> 36:30.080
it's the curb appeal.

36:30.080 --> 36:31.880
The orange paint, the stripes --
it's pretty cool.

36:31.890 --> 36:33.790
When bass and I went to see
the scout, I was like,

36:33.790 --> 36:36.420
"I can flip this right now
and make some quick cash."

36:36.420 --> 36:39.260
but you know what?
I'd like to make a lot of cash

36:39.260 --> 36:41.630
and I was thinking
outside the box.

36:41.630 --> 36:44.260
♪

36:44.260 --> 36:47.000
so, I paid $12,500
for the scout,

36:47.000 --> 36:49.270
I gave the monkeys
a $75,000 budget

36:49.270 --> 36:51.740
but a timeline of only
three weeks to get it finished.

36:51.740 --> 36:53.740
So you're not going up.
You want to go down with this.

36:53.740 --> 36:55.370
I want to get rid
of the four-wheel drive.

36:55.380 --> 36:56.640
Big meat in the back.

36:56.640 --> 36:58.280
When I got the scout
in front of the monkeys,

36:58.280 --> 36:59.910
they didn't really
understand my plan.

36:59.910 --> 37:03.010
Hey, california cruising, pro
touring, whatever you call it.

37:03.020 --> 37:05.520
You know what?
It doesn't exist, buddy!

37:05.520 --> 37:07.490
♪

37:07.490 --> 37:10.460
I was thinking low and lean
and a boulevard cruiser

37:10.460 --> 37:13.360
that could look cool
but also go to the drag strip.

37:13.360 --> 37:14.830
♪

37:14.830 --> 37:16.960
so, my vision for the scout's
a risky one

37:16.960 --> 37:18.960
because it's never been done.

37:18.970 --> 37:21.500
♪

37:21.500 --> 37:22.600
we have a motor.

37:22.600 --> 37:24.200
-Dude, took up the whole crate.
-Nice.

37:24.200 --> 37:25.940
Now, as far as I know,
no one in the world

37:25.940 --> 37:28.340
has ever put a hellcrate
engine into a scout.

37:28.340 --> 37:31.880
So that's 707 horsepower
ripping down the boulevard.

37:31.880 --> 37:35.350
To keep this car cooled down,
we went to ron davis radiator.

37:35.350 --> 37:36.850
That engine sucks a lot of gas,

37:36.850 --> 37:38.450
and you got to have
a good fuel system

37:38.450 --> 37:40.320
pushing it in,
and that is aeromotive.

37:40.320 --> 37:42.690
♪

37:42.690 --> 37:45.560
when it came to stopping
on 707 horsepower,

37:45.560 --> 37:47.690
wilwood brakes did the job.

37:47.690 --> 37:50.830
♪

37:50.830 --> 37:52.700
for the suspension,
we definitely needed to go

37:52.700 --> 37:54.030
with chris alston's
chassisworks,

37:54.030 --> 37:56.030
and we slammed it front and back

37:56.040 --> 37:58.840
along with a four-link,
coilovers all the way around.

37:58.840 --> 38:01.370
And when it came to the wheels,
these are one-off,

38:01.380 --> 38:03.480
one-of-a-kind, designed by us,

38:03.480 --> 38:06.910
and made by revo forged wheels.

38:06.910 --> 38:09.150
When it came to the interior,
I really wanted to stay

38:09.150 --> 38:11.150
with some of the
original appointments,

38:11.150 --> 38:12.580
especially the plaid.

38:12.590 --> 38:15.320
Kind of tipped the hat to what
they did back in the '70s.

38:15.320 --> 38:18.360
And to keep the inside cooled
down, we went to vintage air.

38:18.360 --> 38:20.690
♪

38:20.690 --> 38:22.430
now, when you're building a car
with this much horsepower,

38:22.430 --> 38:25.100
you think, "well, maybe we need
to take the top permanent."

38:25.100 --> 38:26.560
absolutely not.

38:26.570 --> 38:29.500
This thing's a convertible,
and it's staying a convertible.

38:29.500 --> 38:32.070
As far as paint goes, there was
no question in my mind --

38:32.070 --> 38:34.240
keep it orange,
do the factory stripes,

38:34.240 --> 38:38.480
just beef it up a little bit
and make it pop.

38:38.480 --> 38:39.880
So, we got it all done up.

38:39.880 --> 38:41.850
Now all I got to do is find
a buyer with a ton of cash,

38:41.850 --> 38:43.210
and hopefully
I can sell this scout

38:43.220 --> 38:46.020
for something
north of 200 grand.

38:46.020 --> 38:52.060
♪

38:52.060 --> 38:53.660
wait till you see this.

38:53.660 --> 38:58.430
Well, you really can't see it
because, well, it's not here.

38:58.430 --> 39:00.430
It was right there.
Well, that was embarrassing.

39:00.430 --> 39:02.000
I found a buyer
for the '79 scout,

39:02.000 --> 39:03.900
and I don't even know
where it went.

39:03.900 --> 39:05.500
I flew a long way
to get here.

39:05.510 --> 39:08.770
My name's barry richards.
I'm from amherst, ohio.

39:08.780 --> 39:10.840
I'm here in dallas today
at gas monkey garage

39:10.840 --> 39:13.210
to try and make a deal
on a car with richard.

39:13.210 --> 39:16.050
-Is this gonna get better?
-Yeah, it's gonna get better.

39:16.050 --> 39:17.520
Richard:
Barry runs one of the biggest

39:17.520 --> 39:19.620
travelcenters/truck stops
in america,

39:19.620 --> 39:21.690
and they got a lot of them,
and he's got a lot of dough.

39:21.690 --> 39:24.220
I mean, if we were at a poker
table, he would be the whale.

39:24.220 --> 39:26.860
Well, I'm the house,
and I make the rules.

39:26.860 --> 39:31.400
♪

39:31.400 --> 39:33.930
-how's that?
-That is awesome.

39:33.930 --> 39:35.900
Just needed to top off
the gas tank.

39:35.900 --> 39:37.340
That is a fun ride.

39:37.340 --> 39:39.740
Barry: This thing shows up,
the stance is just perfect.

39:39.740 --> 39:41.140
It's mean, it's aggressive.

39:41.140 --> 39:43.240
It's everything a car enthusiast
would want.

39:43.240 --> 39:44.480
Here's the fun part, sir.

39:44.480 --> 39:46.410
We decided it might
ought to have some power.

39:46.410 --> 39:48.680
Oh, no, you didn't.
Look at that.

39:48.680 --> 39:54.020
That's a 2018 hellcrate
motor. 707 horsepower.

39:54.020 --> 39:57.390
Barry really likes the scout,
but I got to take it for a ride.

39:57.390 --> 39:58.690
I mean, the hell scout,

39:58.690 --> 40:00.230
that should shake every quarter
out of his pocket,

40:00.230 --> 40:03.130
which should amount to about
a quarter-million bucks.

40:03.130 --> 40:05.030
[ tires screech ]

40:05.030 --> 40:11.940
♪

40:11.940 --> 40:14.110
[ laughs ]

40:14.110 --> 40:15.740
that didn't take long.

40:15.740 --> 40:18.140
Oh, it'll get on up there
<i> real</i> fast.

40:18.150 --> 40:20.650
Barry:
I'm pretty sure he's gonna want
an outrageous price for it,

40:20.650 --> 40:23.050
and we'll see what happens here.

40:23.050 --> 40:24.420
Richard: Alright, my man.

40:24.420 --> 40:26.580
So, I feel like barry's
pretty much sold on the scout.

40:26.590 --> 40:27.950
Is it fast? Hell yeah.

40:27.950 --> 40:29.290
Is it cool-looking?
Hell yeah.

40:29.290 --> 40:30.890
Is it one-of-a-kind?
Hell yeah.

40:30.890 --> 40:33.630
This is probably one of the
best cars we've ever turned out.

40:33.630 --> 40:35.260
It's definitely
in the top three.

40:35.260 --> 40:38.000
So, as far as the price goes,
I got to tell you, barry,

40:38.000 --> 40:40.630
